Iavan Pijoos, News24(EMPD) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Equipment with an estimated street value of R23 000 used by illegal miners was found in Gugulethu informal settlement in Springs on Tuesday, police said.The equipment included water pumps, gas bottles, wheelbarrows, spades, liquefying pots, and buckets.Lieutenant Colonel Wilfred Kgasago said the suspects fled when police approached a shack where it is suspected gold processing - in this case, sieving gold from mud - takes place.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.